en.content:
Work service long enough and you collect a full bestiary of difficult customers:
the sweet-before, sour-after face-changer;
the walks-in-at-closing closer;
the "my friend got it cheaper" no-record-found type.
Other people collect figurines.
We collect trauma — and not by choice.

"Every other place lets me — you're the only one that won't."
You really do rave about those other places;
you even remember their policies better than they do.
I'm just curious, though:
if everywhere else says yes to everything,
why are you still standing in front of me today?
